Before considering a task complete:

No TypeScript errors — Avoid using any or type assertions to paper over errors.
No ESLint errors or warnings — Avoid adding suppressions.
No Prettier violations — All code must be consistently formatted.
No React console warnings — Including missing keys and invalid prop types.

If any are introduced as a side effect of your changes, fix them before finishing. Do not suppress or ignore issues — resolve the underlying cause.
